  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Liu et al. [53] introduced a spatial weight to highlight the foreground area.",
    "Zhu et al. [75] exploited modality importance using the multi-modal aggregation network.Late fusion.",
    "LF-based methods process both modalities simultaneously, and independent models are built for each modality to make decisions.",
    "Subsequently, the decisions are combined by using weighted summation [4,77,79,81], calculating the joint distribution function [8,76,80], and conducting multi-step localization [78].",
    "Conaire et al. [76] assumed independence between multi-modal data and multiplied the target likelihoods in both modalities to obtain the result."
  ],
